title: [Maelstrom Bay, Bottom]
description: A coral reef blocks the way west.  A colony of spiral gilled tube worms has attached itself to the dead coral of the reef.  Kelp and seaweed undulate sinuously in the current.  A few small silvery fish, thin as stiletto blades, slice through the water among the seaweed.
paths: Obvious exits: north, northeast, east, southeast, south, up
